did.abstract: This collection consists of theses written by students in the School of Education, Health, Nursing, and the Arts Professions from the years 1950-1989.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation

bioghist.head: Historical/Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The New York University School of Education was founded in 1890 as the School of Pedagogy; it was renamed the School of Education in 1921, and thereafter called the School of Education, Health, Nursing, and Arts Professions (SEHNAP) from 1974 to 1994.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of theses written by students in the School of Education, Health, Nursing, and the Arts Professions from the years 1950-1989. They are arranged in one series, neither in alphabetical or chronological order. The title and author's name are both found in the "Description" field. The theses are bound unless noted in brackets after the title (for example: [envelope]). In some instances, two copies of a theses are represented by one entry and noted in brackets after the title (for example: [quantity: 2]).

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is unprocessed and materials remain in original order. Theses are listed by author and title.
The files are grouped into 1 series.
